const DVA_QUESTIONS = [{"cat":"development","q":"You are developing a Lambda function that needs to call a DynamoDB table. The function requires temporary AWS credentials. Which service should you use?","options":["A. IAM User Access Keys","B. IAM Roles with temporary STS credentials","C. Root account credentials","D. Hardcoded AWS Access Keys in the Lambda function"],"answer":0,"explain":"Lambda functions automatically assume an IAM role that provides temporary STS credentials, eliminating the need for hardcoded keys."},{"cat":"security","q":"What is the maximum lifetime of temporary security credentials obtained from STS AssumeRole?","options":["A. 1 hour","B. 12 hours","C. 24 hours","D. 36 hours"],"answer":1,"explain":"Default maximum session duration for STS AssumeRole is 1 hour, but can be extended up to 12 hours depending on the role's maximum session duration setting."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You are setting up a CodePipeline that deploys to EC2 instances using CodeDeploy. Which configuration file must be present in your application?","options":["A. buildspec.yml","B. appspec.yml","C. pipeline.yml","D. deploy.json"],"answer":2,"explain":"CodeDeploy requires an appspec.yml file in the root of your application repository that defines deployment instructions."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"A Lambda function is failing intermittently without proper error messages. Which service should you enable to trace requests and identify bottlenecks?","options":["A. CloudWatch Metrics","B. VPC Flow Logs","C. AWS X-Ray","D. EventBridge"],"answer":3,"explain":"X-Ray provides distributed tracing to visualize request flows through microservices and identify performance issues and errors."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to process 100,000 messages from an SQS queue as quickly as possible. What is the maximum number of messages you can retrieve in a single ReceiveMessage call?","options":["A. 10 messages","B. 25 messages","C. 50 messages","D. 100 messages"],"answer":0,"explain":"SQS ReceiveMessage can retrieve a maximum of 10 messages per call using the MaxNumberOfMessages parameter."},{"cat":"security","q":"You want to store database credentials securely for your application running on EC2. Which service is the best choice?","options":["A. S3 with encryption","B. DynamoDB","C. AWS Secrets Manager","D. Environment variables in launch template"],"answer":1,"explain":"Secrets Manager provides automatic credential rotation, encryption, and centralized management of database credentials."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your CodeDeploy application failed on some instances during deployment. Which deployment strategy allows you to avoid stopping the entire deployment?","options":["A. All at once","B. Half at a time","C. One at a time","D. Canary"],"answer":2,"explain":"Canary deployment gradually routes traffic to new instances, reducing impact if failures occur and allowing rollback."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"CloudWatch Logs shows your Lambda function is timing out. What is the maximum timeout you can set for a Lambda function?","options":["A. 5 minutes","B. 15 minutes","C. 30 minutes","D. 60 minutes"],"answer":3,"explain":"Lambda functions have a maximum timeout of 15 minutes (900 seconds), which must be set during configuration."},{"cat":"development","q":"You are using the AWS SDK to call DynamoDB from a Node.js application. What should you use to improve performance by batching requests?","options":["A. BatchGetItem and BatchWriteItem operations","B. Multiple GetItem calls in parallel","C. Scan and Filter operations","D. Query with pagination tokens"],"answer":0,"explain":"BatchGetItem and BatchWriteItem allow you to batch multiple operations, reducing network round trips and improving throughput."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"You're building a Lambda function that processes image uploads to S3. The function sometimes takes 15 seconds to start after receiving an event. What is the most likely cause and how can you reduce the latency?","options":["A. Increase the timeout to 30 seconds; cold starts are unavoidable","B. Use Lambda provisioned concurrency or ECS fargate for guaranteed performance","C. Enable Lambda cold start reduction with reserved concurrency and code optimization","D. Deploy the function across multiple regions"],"answer":2,"explain":"Cold starts occur on first invocation. Reserved concurrency and provisioned concurrency keep instances warm for consistent performance."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You configured CodePipeline with manual approval stage. A developer manually rejects the deployment. What happens next?","options":["A. The pipeline automatically retries in 5 minutes","B. The pipeline stops and the rejected deployment is discarded","C. The pipeline waits for manual approval again","D. The pipeline rolls back to the previous version"],"answer":2,"explain":"When a manual approval is rejected, the pipeline stops at that stage and the artifact is not promoted further."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your API Gateway returns 403 Forbidden error. Which service should you check for permission issues?","options":["A. VPC Security Groups","B. Network ACLs","C. IAM policies for the calling user/service","D. API Gateway resource policies"],"answer":3,"explain":"403 Forbidden typically indicates lack of permissions, which should be checked in IAM policies attached to the caller."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to call an external API from your Lambda function. The API requires a connection pool. What is the best practice?","options":["A. Create a new connection for each invocation","B. Create a global connection outside the handler and reuse it","C. Use a connection pool service like pgBouncer","D. Store connections in DynamoDB"],"answer":0,"explain":"Creating connections outside the Lambda handler allows them to persist across warm invocations, improving performance."},{"cat":"security","q":"You need to encrypt sensitive data at rest in DynamoDB. How should you enable encryption?","options":["A. Use a Lambda function to encrypt before storing","B. Enable DynamoDB Encryption at rest in table settings","C. Manually encrypt with KMS in your application code","D. Encryption is enabled by default on all DynamoDB tables"],"answer":1,"explain":"DynamoDB supports encryption at rest which can be enabled in table settings; AWS-owned keys are default."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You are deploying to Elastic Beanstalk and need to run database migrations before the new version goes live. Where should you define this?","options":["A. In the buildspec.yml file","B. In the appspec.yml file","C. In the .ebextensions configuration","D. In the CodeDeploy lifecycle"],"answer":2,"explain":"Elastic Beanstalk uses .ebextensions directory for configuration hooks that can run custom commands during deployment."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Lambda logs show high duration times but low CPU usage. What could be the issue?","options":["A. Lambda needs more concurrent executions","B. The function is waiting for I/O operations (database, API calls)","C. CloudWatch is throttling the logs","D. The function needs more memory"],"answer":3,"explain":"High duration with low CPU indicates the function is waiting for I/O operations to complete, not computing."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to send messages to multiple consumers from a single event. Which service is best suited?","options":["A. SQS FIFO","B. SNS with SQS subscribers","C. EventBridge with multiple targets","D. Kinesis Data Stream"],"answer":0,"explain":"SNS (or EventBridge) provides pub/sub messaging that sends messages to multiple subscribers simultaneously."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"A Lambda function asynchronously invokes another Lambda for processing. The invocation fails but the original function completes successfully. How can you ensure the failed invocation is retried?","options":["A. Add retry logic in the calling function","B. Configure SQS dead letter queue (DLQ) as the destination for failed async invocations","C. Use Lambda destinations with SNS for success/failure handling","D. Manually check CloudWatch logs to find failures"],"answer":1,"explain":"Lambda destinations allow async failures to be sent to SQS/SNS for retry and monitoring without explicit function code."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your CodeBuild project uses a buildspec.yml file. Where is this file located in your repository?","options":["A. Must be in the /buildspec directory","B. Must be at the root of the repository","C. Can be at the root or specified in the build project","D. Must be in the .aws directory"],"answer":2,"explain":"buildspec.yml can be at the repository root or in a custom location specified in the CodeBuild project configuration."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"Your Lambda function uses a heavy machine learning library that takes 2 seconds to import. The function is invoked frequently. What approach reduces execution time?","options":["A. Use CloudFront to cache the library","B. Package the library as a Lambda layer and keep the function code minimal","C. Convert the library to WebAssembly","D. Use EC2 instead of Lambda for ML operations"],"answer":1,"explain":"Lambda layers decouple library code from function code, reducing package size and improving cold start times significantly."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"You need to implement conditional writes in DynamoDB where an update only succeeds if an attribute equals a specific value. What parameter enables this?","options":["A. UpdateExpression with SET clause","B. ConditionExpression with attribute_exists() and comparison operator","C. GlobalSecondaryIndex filtering","D. DynamoDB Streams for eventual consistency"],"answer":1,"explain":"ConditionExpression allows atomic conditional updates, preventing race conditions in concurrent write scenarios."},{"cat":"security","q":"You need to allow temporary access to S3 objects without exposing AWS credentials. What should you use?","options":["A. IAM user credentials","B. Hardcoded access keys in URLs","C. Pre-signed URLs","D. Public bucket policies"],"answer":1,"explain":"Pre-signed URLs provide temporary, credential-free access to S3 objects with expiration time limits."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"Your application needs to delete 100 items from DynamoDB table atomically. Using DeleteItem in a loop causes throttling. What is the better approach?","options":["A. Increase provisioned throughput capacity","B. Use BatchWriteItem to delete up to 25 items in a single request","C. Use TTL attributes instead of deleting items","D. Create a new table without those items"],"answer":1,"explain":"BatchWriteItem reduces network overhead and API calls, improving throughput and reducing ProvisionedThroughputExceededException errors."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"A DynamoDB GetItem operation occasionally returns ProvisionedThroughputExceededException even with adequate capacity. What is the most likely issue?","options":["A. The item is too large","B. Hot partition caused by uneven partition key distribution","C. Too many concurrent requests to the same partition key","D. Attribute projection is incorrect"],"answer":1,"explain":"Uneven access to specific partition keys causes hot partitions that exceed that partition's reserved throughput even if table capacity is high."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to store session state across multiple Lambda invocations. Where should you store this data?","options":["A. In a global variable within the Lambda function code","B. In DynamoDB or ElastiCache","C. In the /tmp directory","D. In environment variables"],"answer":0,"explain":"DynamoDB or ElastiCache provide persistent session storage across Lambda invocations and warm starts."},{"cat":"apigateway","q":"You're building a REST API where certain endpoints require transformation of the request body before sending to Lambda. What should be used?","options":["A. Modify Lambda function to handle transformations","B. Use API Gateway request/response transformations with VTL mapping templates","C. Create a middleware EC2 instance","D. Transform in CloudFront edge functions"],"answer":1,"explain":"VTL mapping templates in API Gateway perform request/response transformations without modifying backend logic."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your Elastic Beanstalk application needs to customize the EC2 instances. What should you use?","options":["A. CodeDeploy scripts","B. Lambda functions in the application","C. .ebextensions configuration files","D. SSH to instances and run commands"],"answer":2,"explain":".ebextensions allow you to specify custom configuration and commands that run during Elastic Beanstalk deployment."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"A Step Functions execution is failing on a particular state. Where can you view the exact error message?","options":["A. CloudWatch Metrics dashboard","B. Execution history and state machine logs in the AWS Console","C. Lambda CloudWatch Logs only","D. CodePipeline execution logs"],"answer":3,"explain":"Step Functions execution history shows detailed information about each state and the errors that occurred."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to invoke a Lambda function from another service like S3 or SNS. What must you configure?","options":["A. An API Gateway endpoint in the Lambda function","B. A resource-based policy allowing the service to invoke the Lambda","C. An IAM user with permissions","D. A VPC endpoint"],"answer":0,"explain":"Lambda functions need resource-based policies that explicitly allow services like S3 or SNS to invoke them."},{"cat":"apigateway","q":"An API Gateway endpoint needs to return a mock response for testing without hitting the backend service. How is this configured?","options":["A. Create a Lambda function that returns mock data","B. Set integration type to MOCK and configure VTL response mapping templates","C. Disable the backend integration temporarily","D. Use CloudFormation to create a separate testing API"],"answer":1,"explain":"MOCK integration type with response templates enables rapid testing of API contracts without backend dependencies."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"CodePipeline has stages for Source, Build, and Deploy. What happens if the Build stage fails?","options":["A. The pipeline automatically retries the build","B. The pipeline stops and the Deploy stage is skipped","C. The deploy stage uses the previous build artifact","D. The source stage is re-executed"],"answer":2,"explain":"If any stage in CodePipeline fails, subsequent stages are skipped unless configured otherwise."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your Lambda function is using much more memory than expected during execution. How should you identify the issue?","options":["A. Check Lambda metrics for memory usage","B. Use X-Ray to trace memory allocations in the function","C. Enable CloudWatch detailed monitoring","D. Add console.log statements throughout the code"],"answer":3,"explain":"X-Ray can help identify which parts of your code are consuming the most memory through service maps and traces."},{"cat":"development","q":"You are building a microservice that needs to send messages to multiple independent consumers. Which service best fits this pattern?","options":["A. SQS standard queue","B. SQS FIFO queue","C. SNS topic with multiple subscriptions","D. Kinesis stream"],"answer":0,"explain":"SNS pub/sub pattern sends a message to all subscribers, perfect for multiple independent consumers."},{"cat":"development","q":"Your Lambda function processes file uploads from API Gateway. Files can be 500MB. How should you handle this?","options":["A. Save directly to /tmp in Lambda","B. Use S3 presigned URLs to upload directly from client","C. Use API Gateway to store files","D. Stream files through Lambda to S3"],"answer":1,"explain":"S3 presigned URLs allow clients to upload directly, bypassing Lambda payload limits. Lambda can only handle up to 6MB request payloads and 10MB responses."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You are deploying to ECS using CodePipeline. Which file defines the ECS task definition?","options":["A. buildspec.yml","B. appspec.yml","C. imagedefinitions.json","D. ecs-task-definition.json"],"answer":2,"explain":"imagedefinitions.json is used to specify container image URIs for ECS deployments from CodePipeline."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your DynamoDB query returns items but takes longer than expected. What should you check?","options":["A. Table encryption settings","B. Query filter expressions and indexes","C. VPC configuration","D. Lambda concurrency settings"],"answer":3,"explain":"Query performance can be improved by ensuring you're using appropriate indexes and efficient filter expressions."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to pass data between Lambda functions in a workflow. Which service orchestrates this?","options":["A. EventBridge only","B. SNS topics","C. Step Functions","D. API Gateway"],"answer":0,"explain":"Step Functions orchestrates workflows by coordinating Lambda invocations and passing data between them."},{"cat":"apigateway","q":"Your WebSocket API in API Gateway receives disconnect messages from clients but sometimes the backend Lambda is not invoked. What could cause this?","options":["A. Lambda has insufficient timeout configured","B. IAM role lacks apigateway:ManageConnections permission","C. Invalid route key for disconnect messages","D. WebSocket is not compatible with Lambda"],"answer":2,"explain":"Disconnect route must match the $disconnect system route; custom route names won't trigger on actual disconnects."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your CodeDeploy agent on EC2 instances is not communicating with CodeDeploy service. What should you check?","options":["A. EC2 instance IAM role has CodeDeploy permissions","B. EC2 security group allows outbound HTTPS","C. CodeDeploy agent is installed and running","D. All of the above"],"answer":2,"explain":"All three components are necessary: proper IAM role, network connectivity, and the agent service running."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Lambda cold starts are affecting your application performance. How can you reduce them?","options":["A. Increase Lambda memory allocation","B. Use Lambda provisioned concurrency or keep functions warm with scheduled events","C. Use longer timeouts","D. Store state in environment variables"],"answer":3,"explain":"Provisioned concurrency or periodic invocations keep Lambda functions warm, eliminating cold start latency."},{"cat":"development","q":"You are using AWS SDK to call multiple AWS services. For error handling, what pattern should you follow?","options":["A. Ignore all errors and continue execution","B. Implement try-catch blocks and handle each error appropriately","C. Use Lambda error handling only","D. Rely on automatic retry mechanisms"],"answer":0,"explain":"Proper error handling with try-catch allows you to gracefully handle service errors and implement retry logic."},{"cat":"security","q":"You need to rotate database credentials regularly. Which service automates this?","options":["A. SSM Parameter Store","B. AWS Secrets Manager with rotation","C. CloudFormation","D. CodeCommit"],"answer":1,"explain":"Secrets Manager provides automatic credential rotation for databases and other secrets without application changes."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You are using SAM to deploy a Lambda function with an API Gateway. What does the SAM CLI do?","options":["A. Deploys to production automatically","B. Packages and deploys SAM templates to CloudFormation","C. Only validates YAML syntax","D. Replaces CloudFormation entirely"],"answer":2,"explain":"SAM CLI packages SAM templates and deploys them as CloudFormation stacks to AWS."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"CloudWatch alarm triggered for high error rate on your Lambda function. Where should you look first?","options":["A. EC2 console","B. Lambda CloudWatch Logs for error messages","C. RDS performance insights","D. VPC Flow Logs"],"answer":3,"explain":"CloudWatch Logs for the Lambda function contain detailed error messages and stack traces for debugging."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to invoke a Lambda function from a scheduled event every 5 minutes. Which service should you use?","options":["A. CloudWatch Events (EventBridge)","B. SNS topic","C. SQS queue","D. API Gateway"],"answer":0,"explain":"CloudWatch Events (now EventBridge) can schedule Lambda invocations at specified intervals using cron expressions."},{"cat":"cognito","q":"In Cognito User Pool, you need to customize the confirmation email message sent to users. What trigger should be used?","options":["A. Pre-authentication trigger","B. Custom message trigger to modify message templates","C. Post-confirmation trigger","D. Pre-sign-up trigger"],"answer":1,"explain":"Custom message trigger allows modification of email/SMS content for confirmation, password reset, and other message types."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"CodeBuild project fails with 'Unable to pull image' error. What is the most likely cause?","options":["A. buildspec.yml syntax error","B. Docker image not found in specified registry","C. Insufficient IAM permissions","D. VPC misconfiguration"],"answer":2,"explain":"This error indicates the Docker image URI in the environment configuration is incorrect or inaccessible."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your SQS queue has messages but the Lambda consumer isn't processing them. What could be wrong?","options":["A. SQS event source mapping not configured","B. Lambda function timeout too short","C. Queue permissions not set correctly","D. All of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"Event source mapping must be configured, Lambda must have permissions, and timeout must be sufficient."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to generate a signed URL for an S3 object that expires in 1 hour. How should you do this?","options":["A. Use S3 bucket policy to allow public access","B. Use AWS SDK to generate a pre-signed URL","C. Create an IAM user with S3 access","D. Use CloudFront distribution"],"answer":0,"explain":"AWS SDK's getSignedUrl method generates temporary URLs with automatic expiration and no credential exposure."},{"cat":"security","q":"A developer needs to assume a role in another AWS account. What must be configured?","options":["A. Trust relationship in the target account role","B. IAM policy in source account allowing AssumeRole","C. Both trust relationship and AssumeRole policy","D. Only an IAM user in the target account"],"answer":1,"explain":"Cross-account access requires both trust relationship on the target role and AssumeRole permissions in the source account."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your application needs to store environment-specific configuration (API keys, database URLs). Where should this go?","options":["A. Hardcoded in the application code","B. In deployment artifacts","C. In environment variables or SSM Parameter Store/Secrets Manager","D. In CloudFormation template parameters only"],"answer":2,"explain":"Environment configuration should be stored externally in environment variables or configuration services, never hardcoded."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"API Gateway request is timing out when calling a Lambda function. What is the maximum integration timeout?","options":["A. 3 seconds","B. 15 seconds","C. 29 seconds","D. 60 seconds"],"answer":3,"explain":"API Gateway integration timeout is 29 seconds, regardless of Lambda timeout setting."},{"cat":"development","q":"You are building a real-time data processing application. Which service should you use?","options":["A. SQS","B. Kinesis Data Streams","C. SNS","D. S3"],"answer":0,"explain":"Kinesis Data Streams is designed for real-time streaming and processing of data at scale."},{"cat":"cognito","q":"A Cognito User Pool needs to enforce multi-factor authentication (MFA) for users in the 'admin' group. Where should this policy be defined?","options":["A. User Pool policies section","B. Pre-authentication Lambda trigger to check group membership and enforce MFA","C. Cognito Identity Pool role mapping","D. IAM policy attached to user account"],"answer":1,"explain":"Pre-authentication trigger can inspect user groups and challenge users for MFA before authentication succeeds."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your Elastic Beanstalk environment needs to execute a custom script before each deployment. What file should you create?","options":["A. hooks/predeploy.sh in .ebextensions","B. scripts/deploy.sh in the root","C. container_commands in .ebextensions/01_setup.config","D. prebuild.sh in buildspec.yml"],"answer":2,"explain":"container_commands in .ebextensions configuration files execute at the end of the deployment process."},{"cat":"sqs","q":"Your SQS queue processes orders and needs to include order ID and priority with each message. What is the appropriate mechanism?","options":["A. Put order ID and priority in the message body as plain text","B. Use message attributes to store structured metadata like order ID and priority","C. Create separate queues for different priority levels","D. Store metadata in DynamoDB with message ID"],"answer":1,"explain":"Message attributes provide structured metadata storage without polluting the message body, enabling filtering and sorting."},{"cat":"development","q":"You are implementing a recommendation engine that fetches user history from DynamoDB and makes decisions. Some queries timeout under load. What should you implement?","options":["A. Increase DynamoDB read capacity","B. Add DAX (DynamoDB Accelerator) caching layer","C. Query only first 100 items","D. Move to RDS"],"answer":1,"explain":"DAX provides microsecond-level caching for DynamoDB, significantly reducing query latency for frequently accessed items without changing application code."},{"cat":"sqs","q":"You need to send 50 messages to SQS in your application. Individual SendMessage calls cause high latency. What operation should be used?","options":["A. Use SendMessage in a loop","B. Use SendMessageBatch to send up to 10 messages per request","C. Use PutMessage instead of SendMessage","D. Buffer in DynamoDB first, then send to SQS"],"answer":1,"explain":"SendMessageBatch reduces API calls and latency by bundling up to 10 messages into a single request."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You are deploying a web application to multiple EC2 instances. CodeDeploy is using 'OneAtATime' deployment strategy. What is the impact?","options":["A. All instances are stopped and replaced simultaneously","B. Instances are deployed one at a time, minimizing service disruption","C. Half the instances are deployed at a time","D. A percentage of traffic is shifted to new instances"],"answer":2,"explain":"'OneAtATime' deployment ensures minimal disruption by replacing instances sequentially."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your CloudWatch alarm keeps triggering false positives. What metric should you adjust?","options":["A. CloudWatch Logs retention","B. Alarm threshold and evaluation periods","C. Lambda memory","D. VPC network ACLs"],"answer":3,"explain":"Adjust alarm thresholds, evaluation periods, and datapoints to reduce false positives."},{"cat":"sqs","q":"Your SQS consumer polls the queue every 0.1 seconds but usually gets 0 messages. This causes high API call costs. What optimization reduces costs?","options":["A. Increase polling frequency to every 1 second","B. Enable long polling with WaitTimeSeconds=20 to reduce empty responses","C. Use SNS instead of SQS","D. Reduce message visibility timeout"],"answer":1,"explain":"Long polling waits up to 20 seconds for messages before returning, dramatically reducing API calls and associated costs."},{"cat":"codedeploy","q":"You're deploying a Lambda function with CodeDeploy and need to validate the new version before shifting all traffic. What AppSpec hooks enable this?","options":["A. BeforeDeploy and AfterDeploy hooks","B. BeforeAllowTraffic to validate and AfterAllowTraffic to confirm","C. PreHook and PostHook","D. StartHook and EndHook"],"answer":1,"explain":"Lambda deployment hooks allow validation of the new version (BeforeAllowTraffic) before shifting traffic (AfterAllowTraffic)."},{"cat":"codedeploy","q":"A CodeDeploy Lambda deployment uses Linear traffic shifting with 10% per minute. The deployment takes 15 minutes total. What is the traffic progression?","options":["A. 10%, 20%, 30%... 100% over 10 minutes","B. 10% every minute: 10%, 20%, 30%... 100% over 10 minutes","C. All traffic shifts to new version immediately","D. Traffic stays at 50/50 mix"],"answer":0,"explain":"Linear traffic shifting increments traffic by a fixed percentage each interval, allowing incremental validation."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"DynamoDB return value shows 'ProvisionedThroughputExceededException'. What happened?","options":["A. Your table schema is wrong","B. You exceeded the provisioned read/write capacity","C. The item size is too large","D. Your GSI is misconfigured"],"answer":3,"explain":"ProvisionedThroughputExceededException means requests exceeded the table's capacity units."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to call the AWS SDK from your Lambda function. How should you structure your code?","options":["A. Instantiate SDK client inside the handler function","B. Instantiate SDK client outside the handler for reuse across invocations","C. Use a Lambda layer for the SDK","D. The SDK is automatically available in Lambda"],"answer":0,"explain":"Instantiating clients outside the handler reuses connections across invocations, improving performance."},{"cat":"security","q":"A developer asks to store an API key in a Lambda environment variable. What should you advise?","options":["A. OK, environment variables are encrypted","B. No, use Secrets Manager or Parameter Store instead","C. OK, but only if marked as sensitive","D. Environment variables are the most secure option"],"answer":1,"explain":"Secrets Manager and Parameter Store provide better security with encryption, rotation, and audit logging."},{"cat":"cloudformation","q":"You're using CloudFormation to deploy a serverless application. What AWS::Serverless resource defines an API endpoint?","options":["A. AWS::Serverless::Function","B. AWS::Serverless::Api with properties for routes and integrations","C. AWS::Serverless::Endpoint","D. AWS::ApiGateway::RestApi"],"answer":1,"explain":"AWS::Serverless::Api (SAM) is the simplified CloudFormation resource for API Gateway with automatic integration to Lambda."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your Lambda function is making HTTP calls to an external API. You see timeout errors. What could be wrong?","options":["A. Lambda is in a VPC without NAT gateway","B. External API is unreachable","C. Lambda timeout is too short","D. All of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"All three factors can cause timeout errors: network configuration, API availability, and function timeout."},{"cat":"development","q":"You are using DynamoDB and need consistent reads for critical operations. What should you enable?","options":["A. Read replicas","B. Strong consistency in GetItem/Query/Scan","C. DynamoDB streams","D. Global secondary indexes"],"answer":0,"explain":"Strong consistency ensures you read the latest data, though with higher latency and cost."},{"cat":"development","q":"Your Lambda function calls third-party APIs that occasionally timeout. You need retry logic with backoff. Which AWS SDK feature should you use?","options":["A. Implement custom retry loops with setTimeout","B. Configure retry strategy in SDK client configuration","C. Use Step Functions for retry orchestration","D. Wrap with SQS for automatic retries"],"answer":1,"explain":"AWS SDK provides configurable retry strategies with exponential backoff and jitter built-in, eliminating the need for custom retry logic."},{"cat":"cloudformation","q":"A SAM template needs to grant a Lambda function permissions to read from S3 and write to DynamoDB. What section should be used?","options":["A. ManagedPolicyArns with AWS managed policies","B. Policies section with SAM policy templates like S3ReadPolicy and DynamoDBWritePolicy","C. IAM section of the template","D. Resource section for each AWS service"],"answer":1,"explain":"SAM policy templates provide shorthand permissions (e.g., S3ReadPolicy) without writing full IAM policy documents."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"S3 bucket policy allows public read access, but users still get 403 Forbidden. What could block access?","options":["A. ACL on individual objects","B. VPC endpoint misconfiguration","C. CloudFront origin access identity","D. S3 encryption settings"],"answer":3,"explain":"Object ACLs can override bucket policy, blocking access even if the bucket is publicly readable."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to filter and transform messages from SQS before processing. What approach is best?","options":["A. Use SQS filter policy on the queue","B. Process all messages and filter in Lambda","C. Use SNS with SQS and SNS filter policy","D. Create multiple SQS queues"],"answer":0,"explain":"SNS filter policies allow filtering messages before they reach the SQS queue, reducing processing."},{"cat":"elasticache","q":"Your application caches user sessions in ElastiCache Redis. When the cache is cold, database load spikes. What caching pattern mitigates this?","options":["A. Write-through: always write to cache and database together","B. Lazy loading: populate cache on cache miss, avoiding stampedes","C. Cache invalidation: clear cache periodically","D. TTL only without application-side caching"],"answer":0,"explain":"Write-through ensures database and cache are always in sync, preventing cache misses and database flooding."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You need to perform a zero-downtime deployment. Which CodeDeploy strategy is best?","options":["A. AllAtOnce","B. HalfAtATime","C. OneAtATime or Canary","D. None, CodeDeploy doesn't support zero-downtime"],"answer":2,"explain":"OneAtATime and Canary strategies minimize downtime by gradually updating instances."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your Step Functions execution shows a state timing out. What is the default Step Functions timeout?","options":["A. 5 minutes","B. 1 year","C. No timeout by default","D. 15 minutes"],"answer":3,"explain":"Step Functions default timeout is 1 year unless you set a TimeoutSeconds in the state machine definition."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to process images uploaded to S3. Which event notification method is preferred?","options":["A. Polling S3 ListObjects every minute","B. S3 Event Notifications to SQS or Lambda","C. CloudTrail for S3 API calls","D. CloudWatch metrics monitoring"],"answer":0,"explain":"S3 Event Notifications trigger Lambda or SQS immediately when objects are uploaded."},{"cat":"security","q":"A third-party application needs temporary access to your S3 bucket. What should you use?","options":["A. IAM user with long-term credentials","B. STS AssumeRole with temporary credentials","C. Root account credentials","D. Bucket policy allowing public access"],"answer":1,"explain":"STS AssumeRole provides temporary, time-limited credentials that can be revoked immediately."},{"cat":"elasticache","q":"An ElastiCache cluster has an eviction policy of allkeys-lru (evict any key using LRU). Application performance degrades after memory is full. What is happening?","options":["A. The cluster is undersized and needs larger instance type","B. Keys are being evicted when memory is full, causing increased cache misses and database hits","C. LRU policy is not effective for session data","D. Memory usage monitoring is not enabled"],"answer":1,"explain":"eviction-lru removes least recently used keys when maxmemory is exceeded, increasing cache misses and database load."},{"cat":"kinesis","q":"You're streaming clickstream data to Kinesis with millions of users. Each record contains user ID. How should partition keys be chosen?","options":["A. Use timestamp as partition key for temporal ordering","B. Use user ID as partition key to distribute load evenly","C. Use a random value to load-balance across shards","D. Use the same key for all records"],"answer":1,"explain":"User ID as partition key distributes traffic across shards and keeps a user's events on the same shard for ordering."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to implement API authentication without managing users. Which service should you use?","options":["A. Lambda authorizer (custom)","B. API Key authentication","C. Cognito User Pool with API Gateway","D. IAM authorization"],"answer":0,"explain":"Cognito User Pool integrates with API Gateway to manage user authentication without custom logic."},{"cat":"kinesis","q":"A Kinesis consumer needs to read all records from the beginning of a stream. What GetShardIterator type should be used?","options":["A. LATEST to get the newest records","B. TRIM_HORIZON to read from the oldest retained record","C. AT_TIMESTAMP to read from a specific time","D. NEW_IMAGE to get only changed records"],"answer":1,"explain":"TRIM_HORIZON (oldest retained record, typically 24 hours) is used for complete replays; LATEST starts from new records."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your Elastic Beanstalk application needs to run worker tasks in the background. What should you use?","options":["A. Additional EC2 instances","B. SQS with worker environment tier","C. Lambda functions","D. CodeDeploy"],"answer":2,"explain":"Elastic Beanstalk Worker environment tier automatically pulls messages from SQS and runs them."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"DynamoDB table shows low throughput despite high provisioned capacity. What could cause this?","options":["A. Hot partition due to uneven key distribution","B. Too many indexes on the table","C. Encryption overhead","D. CloudWatch Logs consuming capacity"],"answer":3,"explain":"Hot partitions occur when many requests target the same partition key, causing throttling despite high capacity."},{"cat":"development","q":"You are building a serverless application with Lambda and need persistent storage for application state. What should you use?","options":["A. Lambda /tmp directory","B. DynamoDB or RDS","C. S3 with versioning","D. CloudWatch Logs"],"answer":0,"explain":"DynamoDB or RDS provide persistent, reliable storage for application state across Lambda invocations."},{"cat":"xray","q":"Your microservices are instrumented with X-Ray. A distributed trace shows long latency in the downstream service. How should you trace internal operations?","options":["A. Use X-Ray annotations to tag high-level information","B. Create X-Ray subsegments to measure specific operations within the service","C. Add more logging to CloudWatch","D. Use CloudTrail to audit API calls"],"answer":1,"explain":"Subsegments break down service execution into named operations (database queries, API calls), revealing where latency occurs."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You need to deploy Lambda functions with infrastructure as code. Should you use CloudFormation or SAM?","options":["A. CloudFormation only","B. SAM for simpler Lambda-focused deployments","C. Both are equivalent","D. Neither, use the Console"],"answer":2,"explain":"SAM provides Lambda-specific optimizations and simpler syntax, while CloudFormation is more general."},{"cat":"xray","q":"You need to filter X-Ray traces to see only those with errors. Where should error information be added to the trace?","options":["A. In the response object returned to the client","B. Add error=true as metadata in the trace segment","C. Use CloudWatch Logs Insights to search error traces","D. Use annotations with error flags for filtering"],"answer":3,"explain":"Annotations are indexed and filterable in X-Ray console, making them ideal for error flags, status codes, and custom tags."},{"cat":"development","q":"You are building a real-time notification system where Lambda processes events from EventBridge. Some Lambda invocations occasionally fail transiently. How should you handle this?","options":["A. Let EventBridge automatically retry up to 2 times by default","B. Configure a Dead Letter Queue (DLQ) target in EventBridge","C. Add manual retry logic in Lambda","D. Both A and B"],"answer":3,"explain":"EventBridge automatically retries failed targets; configure a DLQ to capture failures after retries exhausted for further investigation and processing."},{"cat":"s3","q":"You want S3 to automatically notify a Lambda function whenever a new image file is uploaded. How should this be configured?","options":["A. Use S3 event notifications with Lambda destination","B. Enable S3 versioning to track new uploads","C. Use CloudWatch Events to poll S3","D. Manually invoke Lambda after each upload"],"answer":0,"explain":"S3 event notifications (ObjectCreated) can trigger Lambda directly when matching objects are uploaded."},{"cat":"s3","q":"Your S3 bucket has objects with different retention requirements: 30 days for logs, 1 year for archives. How are these enforced?","options":["A. Use bucket policies to prevent deletion","B. Apply S3 lifecycle rules with different prefixes or tags for each retention period","C. Manually delete old objects","D. Use S3 Glacier for all objects"],"answer":1,"explain":"Lifecycle rules can transition/delete objects based on age and tags, automating retention policy enforcement."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"You're building a Lambda function that processes image uploads to S3. The function sometimes takes 15 seconds to start after receiving an event. What is the most likely cause and how can you reduce the latency?","options":["A. Increase the timeout to 30 seconds; cold starts are unavoidable","B. Use Lambda provisioned concurrency or ECS fargate for guaranteed performance","C. Enable Lambda cold start reduction with reserved concurrency and code optimization","D. Deploy the function across multiple regions"],"answer":2,"explain":"Cold starts occur on first invocation. Reserved concurrency and provisioned concurrency keep instances warm for consistent performance."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"A Lambda function asynchronously invokes another Lambda for processing. The invocation fails but the original function completes successfully. How can you ensure the failed invocation is retried?","options":["A. Add retry logic in the calling function","B. Configure SQS dead letter queue (DLQ) as the destination for failed async invocations","C. Use Lambda destinations with SNS for success/failure handling","D. Manually check CloudWatch logs to find failures"],"answer":1,"explain":"Lambda destinations allow async failures to be sent to SQS/SNS for retry and monitoring without explicit function code."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"Your Lambda function uses a heavy machine learning library that takes 2 seconds to import. The function is invoked frequently. What approach reduces execution time?","options":["A. Use CloudFront to cache the library","B. Package the library as a Lambda layer and keep the function code minimal","C. Convert the library to WebAssembly","D. Use EC2 instead of Lambda for ML operations"],"answer":1,"explain":"Lambda layers decouple library code from function code, reducing package size and improving cold start times significantly."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"You need to ensure a Lambda function has at least 100 concurrent invocations available at all times for critical workload. What configuration prevents scaling delays?","options":["A. Increase timeout to ensure functions complete","B. Use reserved concurrency set to 100 to keep capacity warm","C. Use Spot instances for Lambda","D. Enable concurrent execution without limits"],"answer":1,"explain":"Reserved concurrency guarantees minimum available concurrency, preventing throttling and cold starts for critical applications."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"Your Lambda function calls external APIs with synchronous invocation. If the API times out, the function fails. How should this be handled with async patterns?","options":["A. Increase Lambda timeout to match API timeout","B. Use SQS intermediate queue for async invocation with error retry mechanism","C. Call the API multiple times in parallel","D. Use Step Functions instead"],"answer":1,"explain":"SQS provides automatic retries, dead-letter handling, and decouples caller from external API failures."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to implement distributed tracing across microservices. Which service should you use?","options":["A. CloudWatch Logs","B. AWS X-Ray","C. EventBridge","D. CloudWatch Metrics"],"answer":0,"explain":"X-Ray provides distributed tracing and visualization of request flows through microservices."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"A Lambda function's memory is set to 128MB but processing a 500MB file causes memory errors. Moving to 3008MB fixes it but increases cost. What is the optimal approach?","options":["A. Keep 3008MB since it now works","B. Stream the file using chunked reading with 512MB memory, reducing cost while handling large files","C. Split the file into smaller parts externally","D. Use Glue instead of Lambda"],"answer":1,"explain":"Streaming/chunking allows processing large files with modest memory; reading entire files into memory is inefficient."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your Elastic Beanstalk application needs different configurations per environment. How should you handle this?","options":["A. Create separate EB environments with environment-specific .ebextensions","B. Hardcode values in the application","C. Use environment variables set in EB configuration","D. A and C"],"answer":2,"explain":"Combine environment-specific .ebextensions with environment variables for flexible configuration."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"You deploy a Lambda function that reads secrets from Secrets Manager on every invocation. Latency is high and API calls are expensive. What optimization helps?","options":["A. Cache secrets in the function initialization code outside the handler","B. Move to environment variables","C. Use IAM roles instead of secrets","D. Pre-load all secrets into DynamoDB"],"answer":0,"explain":"Initialization code runs once per container; caching secrets there avoids repeated API calls across warm invocations."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to cache API responses to reduce latency. Which service should you use?","options":["A. DynamoDB","B. ElastiCache","C. S3","D. RDS"],"answer":0,"explain":"ElastiCache provides in-memory caching for frequently accessed data with low latency."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"A Lambda function uses provisioned concurrency set to 10. However, peak traffic requires 50 concurrent invocations. What should happen to additional invocations beyond 10?","options":["A. All requests are throttled","B. 10 use provisioned (warm), 40 more scale up with auto-scaling (may experience cold starts)","C. The function is queued indefinitely","D. Only 10 requests are processed; rest are dropped"],"answer":1,"explain":"Provisioned concurrency starts 10 warm instances; excess traffic auto-scales with potential cold starts beyond provisioned level."},{"cat":"development","q":"Your DynamoDB table has millions of items. You need to query by both userId and status. You already have a GSI on userId. Should you add another GSI on status?","options":["A. Yes, add GSI on status","B. No, create a GSI on (userId, status) composite key","C. Create LSI on status instead","D. Use scan with filter"],"answer":1,"explain":"A composite GSI with userId as partition key and status as sort key enables efficient queries on both attributes without additional indexes."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your X-Ray service map shows a Lambda function with high error rate. How should you investigate?","options":["A. Check X-Ray traces for the Lambda","B. Review CloudWatch Logs for the Lambda","C. Look at Lambda metrics in CloudWatch","D. All of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"Complete investigation requires X-Ray traces, CloudWatch Logs, and CloudWatch metrics."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"You configure a Lambda function with destinations for success (SNS) and failure (SQS DLQ). An async invocation succeeds; which destination receives the event?","options":["A. Both SNS and SQS","B. Only SNS because it's configured for success","C. Only SQS because it's a DLQ","D. Neither; destinations are for errors only"],"answer":1,"explain":"Destinations route based on invocation outcome: success events go to success destination, failures to the DLQ destination."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"Your Lambda function is URL-based for easy invocation. The invoker is in a different AWS account. What permission must be granted?","options":["A. Lambda:InvokeFunction only","B. Lambda:InvokeFunctionUrl permission to the other account","C. Full S3 access to both accounts","D. No permission needed for same region"],"answer":1,"explain":"Cross-account Lambda URL invocation requires explicit lambda:InvokeFunctionUrl permission in the function's resource-based policy."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You are deploying a web application to Fargate. Which networking configuration is required?","options":["A. EC2 security groups","B. VPC, subnet, and security group for the task","C. Network ACLs only","D. Fargate doesn't require network configuration"],"answer":2,"explain":"Fargate tasks require VPC configuration with subnets and security groups for network connectivity."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"API Gateway method call shows a sudden increase in latency. What could cause this?","options":["A. Backend Lambda scaling up","B. Network congestion","C. Database query optimization issues","D. Any of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"Latency increases can come from Lambda cold starts, network issues, or database bottlenecks."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to process CSV file uploads asynchronously. What architecture should you use?","options":["A. Upload directly to Lambda","B. S3 upload triggering Lambda via event notification","C. API Gateway endpoint with SQS","D. CodeCommit repository"],"answer":0,"explain":"S3 event notifications trigger Lambda to process uploaded files immediately without synchronous waiting."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"A Lambda function processes events from DynamoDB Streams but some events are missed. The batch window and batch size settings are default. What could cause missed events?","options":["A. DynamoDB Streams has insufficient capacity","B. Lambda concurrency is set too low for stream shards; increase concurrent execution or shard count","C. Batch window is too large","D. Events are automatically deleted after 1 hour"],"answer":1,"explain":"DynamoDB Streams source mapping has one invocation per shard; low concurrency causes single-shard backlog and event loss."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your CodePipeline needs to approve deployments based on manual review. Where should you add this?","options":["A. In the Source stage","B. In the Build stage","C. As a separate stage with Manual approval action","D. In the Deploy stage only"],"answer":2,"explain":"Manual approval is a separate stage action that stops the pipeline for human review."},{"cat":"lambda","q":"You need to invoke a Lambda function from a Kinesis stream but want to filter records before invocation. Where should filtering happen?","options":["A. Inside the Lambda function","B. Configure filter policies in the event source mapping to reduce invocations","C. Pre-filter in Kinesis","D. Use CloudWatch Events to filter"],"answer":1,"explain":"Event source mapping filter policies allow server-side filtering, reducing unnecessary Lambda invocations and costs."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to generate unique IDs for database records. What is the best approach?","options":["A. Use DynamoDB auto-incrementing IDs","B. Use DynamoDB with UUID generation","C. Use RDS with SERIAL type","D. Generate UUIDs in application code"],"answer":0,"explain":"DynamoDB doesn't auto-increment; use UUID generation in application code or use separate counter table."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"You need to implement conditional writes in DynamoDB where an update only succeeds if an attribute equals a specific value. What parameter enables this?","options":["A. UpdateExpression with SET clause","B. ConditionExpression with attribute_exists() and comparison operator","C. GlobalSecondaryIndex filtering","D. DynamoDB Streams for eventual consistency"],"answer":1,"explain":"ConditionExpression allows atomic conditional updates, preventing race conditions in concurrent write scenarios."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your Lambda function needs to access another AWS service. What should you configure?","options":["A. Environment variables with service endpoints","B. IAM role with permissions for that service","C. VPC endpoint to the service","D. Lambda layer with service SDK"],"answer":2,"explain":"IAM role attached to Lambda must have permissions for the services it needs to call."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your application metrics show DynamoDB read throttling. What is the best solution?","options":["A. Increase provisioned read capacity","B. Enable auto-scaling on the table","C. Use DAX caching for frequently accessed items","D. Any of the above depending on the pattern"],"answer":3,"explain":"Solutions depend on access patterns: scale capacity, auto-scale, or use caching strategically."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"Your application needs to delete 100 items from DynamoDB table atomically. Using DeleteItem in a loop causes throttling. What is the better approach?","options":["A. Increase provisioned throughput capacity","B. Use BatchWriteItem to delete up to 25 items in a single request","C. Use TTL attributes instead of deleting items","D. Create a new table without those items"],"answer":1,"explain":"BatchWriteItem reduces network overhead and API calls, improving throughput and reducing ProvisionedThroughputExceededException errors."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"A DynamoDB GetItem operation occasionally returns ProvisionedThroughputExceededException even with adequate capacity. What is the most likely issue?","options":["A. The item is too large","B. Hot partition caused by uneven partition key distribution","C. Too many concurrent requests to the same partition key","D. Attribute projection is incorrect"],"answer":1,"explain":"Uneven access to specific partition keys causes hot partitions that exceed that partition's reserved throughput even if table capacity is high."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to process a stream of IoT sensor data with Lambda. Events come frequently. Some processing takes longer than expected, causing queue buildup. What should you configure?","options":["A. Increase Lambda memory","B. Increase Lambda timeout","C. Increase the batch size for event source mapping","D. Decrease batch window to process faster"],"answer":2,"explain":"Larger batches allow Lambda to process more events per invocation, reducing the number of invocations needed and improving throughput for streaming workloads."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"You're designing a DynamoDB table for user sessions where SessionId is the partition key. Users are distributed globally. Why might a few users experience throttling while others don't?","options":["A. Network latency for distant regions","B. Some session IDs hash to the same partition, creating hot partitions with uneven load","C. Users with longer sessions use more throughput","D. Backup operations are running"],"answer":1,"explain":"Partition key distribution matters; poor distribution leads to hot partitions and throttling despite adequate total capacity."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"A DynamoDB table uses on-demand billing. Traffic spikes cause occasional throttling. What is the cause and solution?","options":["A. On-demand should never throttle","B. On-demand billing mode has adaptive throughput limits; exceeding limits causes throttling - use provisioned with auto-scaling","C. The partition key is poorly chosen","D. Items are too large"],"answer":1,"explain":"Even on-demand billing has throughput limits (40,000 RCU/WCU per partition key); sustained spikes require provisioned capacity."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"You need to atomically increment a counter in DynamoDB without reading the current value. What operation should be used?","options":["A. GetItem then UpdateItem separately","B. UpdateExpression with SET counter = counter + :val","C. Query to get current value then write","D. Use Lambda for atomic increment"],"answer":1,"explain":"UpdateExpression with SET allows atomic server-side increment without read-modify-write race conditions."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"Your DynamoDB query retrieves 100 items but you only need 10. Each item is 10KB. The query returns all 100. How is this optimized?","options":["A. Query returns items as needed; no optimization possible","B. Add Limit parameter to the query to retrieve only 10 items upfront","C. Remove unused attributes from the table","D. Use ProjectionExpression to exclude large attributes"],"answer":1,"explain":"Limit parameter stops retrieval after N items, reducing data transfer and improving query latency and cost."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Lambda function throws 'Unable to import module' error. What is the likely cause?","options":["A. Missing IAM permissions","B. Missing dependency in Lambda layer or deployment package","C. Incorrect handler configuration","D. Lambda timeout"],"answer":3,"explain":"This error means a required module/library is not available in the Lambda package or layer."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to ensure your Lambda function doesn't exceed memory limits. What should you do?","options":["A. Always allocate maximum memory","B. Monitor CloudWatch metrics and optimize code","C. Use Lambda layers for all code","D. Split code across multiple functions"],"answer":0,"explain":"Monitor metrics, identify memory leaks, and optimize code to stay within limits and reduce costs."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"A DynamoDB table has a Global Secondary Index (GSI) on a sparse attribute (present in 5% of items). Queries on the GSI are slow. What is the issue?","options":["A. GSI only works on frequently used attributes","B. GSI on sparse attributes can cause hot partitions if sparse attribute values are unevenly distributed","C. GSI are always slower than queries on main table","D. Table size is too large"],"answer":1,"explain":"Sparse attributes in GSI can lead to skewed partition distribution if values cluster; normal queries are better for sparse data."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your Elastic Beanstalk health check shows degraded status. What should you check?","options":["A. Enhanced health reporting logs","B. Application logs in CloudWatch","C. EC2 instance status","D. All of the above"],"answer":2,"explain":"Investigate health checks across enhanced health reporting, application logs, and instance status."},{"cat":"development","q":"Your API needs to generate documents (PDFs) on demand. Documents can take 30+ seconds to generate. Clients expect fast responses. What architecture should you use?","options":["A. Generate synchronously in Lambda","B. Invoke Lambda asynchronously, store in S3, return presigned URL immediately","C. Use Step Functions to coordinate generation","D. Use EC2 for document processing"],"answer":1,"explain":"Asynchronous processing with S3 storage and presigned URLs provides fast API responses while generating documents in the background."},{"cat":"development","q":"You are refactoring a monolith into microservices using Lambda. Service A needs to call Service B synchronously. What should you use to handle transient failures?","options":["A. Direct HTTP calls with exponential backoff","B. SQS for reliable async messaging","C. SQS with Lambda long polling","D. Step Functions for orchestration"],"answer":0,"explain":"For synchronous service-to-service calls with transient failures, HTTP with SDK retry strategy and exponential backoff is appropriate."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"You need to fetch items from multiple logical groups in a single request. DynamoDB supports this via what operation?","options":["A. Query with multiple partition keys","B. BatchGetItem to retrieve items from different partitions in one request","C. Scan with filters","D. Global Secondary Index"],"answer":1,"explain":"BatchGetItem allows fetching up to 100 items across different partition keys in a single request, more efficient than individual GetItems."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You need to deploy Lambda functions with dependencies. What is the best practice?","options":["A. Include all dependencies in the deployment package","B. Use Lambda layers for dependencies","C. Install dependencies at runtime in the function","D. Upload dependencies to S3"],"answer":2,"explain":"Lambda layers provide a clean way to manage shared dependencies across multiple functions."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"A DynamoDB stream is configured with NEW_AND_OLD_IMAGES view type. A Lambda consumer processes stream records but only needs to know what changed, not the full record. What attribute provides this?","options":["A. DynamoDBStreamRecord.dynamodb.Keys only","B. Use DynamoDBStreamRecord.dynamodb.OldImage and NewImage to compute diff","C. Streams don't support change detection","D. Use CloudTrail instead"],"answer":1,"explain":"Comparing OldImage and NewImage reveals attribute changes; DynamoDB Streams don't provide explicit deltas."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"Your application uses both strong consistency (immediately after write) and eventual consistency reads. How should consistency be configured per query?","options":["A. Set ConsistentRead=true for strong consistency in GetItem or Query","B. Use a separate table for consistent reads","C. DynamoDB handles consistency automatically","D. Strong consistency is not available"],"answer":0,"explain":"ConsistentRead parameter in GetItem/Query/BatchGetItem enables strong vs eventual consistency per operation."},{"cat":"dynamodb","q":"You're implementing a leaderboard that must show top 100 scores globally. Scores are stored in DynamoDB with UserId as partition key. How should queries work efficiently?","options":["A. Query UserId then scan all items","B. Create GSI with Score as partition key, sorted by Score descending, then Query and limit to 100","C. Scan the entire table and sort in application","D. Use Redshift for leaderboards"],"answer":1,"explain":"GSI with partition key on Score allows efficient ranking queries without scanning the entire table."},{"cat":"development","q":"Your Lambda function uses a database connection pool that is being reinitialized on every invocation causing performance degradation. How should you fix this?","options":["A. Increase Lambda memory","B. Move connection pool initialization outside the handler (into global scope)","C. Use RDS Proxy instead","D. Use DynamoDB instead of database"],"answer":1,"explain":"Lambda reuses container instances across invocations. Initializing resources outside the handler ensures they persist across calls within the same container."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your Step Functions state machine has a state that never exits. What could cause this?","options":["A. Missing End: true","B. Infinite loop in state transitions","C. Task state never completes","D. All of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"Investigate state definitions, transitions, and task completion for hanging state machines."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to send a message to multiple SQS queues from Lambda. Currently you are making sequential calls. How should you optimize this?","options":["A. Use SQS batch SendMessage API","B. Use SNS to fan out to multiple SQS queues","C. Create multiple Lambda functions","D. Use DynamoDB Streams instead"],"answer":1,"explain":"SNS fanout pattern sends a single message to multiple SQS queues, and SNS batch API reduces API calls compared to sequential queue writes."},{"cat":"apigateway","q":"You're building a REST API where certain endpoints require transformation of the request body before sending to Lambda. What should be used?","options":["A. Modify Lambda function to handle transformations","B. Use API Gateway request/response transformations with VTL mapping templates","C. Create a middleware EC2 instance","D. Transform in CloudFront edge functions"],"answer":1,"explain":"VTL mapping templates in API Gateway perform request/response transformations without modifying backend logic."},{"cat":"apigateway","q":"An API Gateway endpoint needs to return a mock response for testing without hitting the backend service. How is this configured?","options":["A. Create a Lambda function that returns mock data","B. Set integration type to MOCK and configure VTL response mapping templates","C. Disable the backend integration temporarily","D. Use CloudFormation to create a separate testing API"],"answer":1,"explain":"MOCK integration type with response templates enables rapid testing of API contracts without backend dependencies."},{"cat":"apigateway","q":"Your WebSocket API in API Gateway receives disconnect messages from clients but sometimes the backend Lambda is not invoked. What could cause this?","options":["A. Lambda has insufficient timeout configured","B. IAM role lacks apigateway:ManageConnections permission","C. Invalid route key for disconnect messages","D. WebSocket is not compatible with Lambda"],"answer":2,"explain":"Disconnect route must match the $disconnect system route; custom route names won't trigger on actual disconnects."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to store configuration that changes frequently. Where should you store it?","options":["A. In the Lambda function code","B. In CloudFormation parameters","C. In SSM Parameter Store or AppConfig","D. In hardcoded environment variables"],"answer":0,"explain":"SSM Parameter Store and AppConfig allow dynamic configuration changes without code redeployment."},{"cat":"apigateway","q":"You're implementing API rate limiting to protect against abuse. Which API Gateway feature controls requests per time period?","options":["A. Throttling with RateLimit and BurstLimit settings","B. Usage Plans with quota and rate settings","C. VPC Endpoint policies","D. WAF rules only"],"answer":0,"explain":"RateLimit (requests per second) and BurstLimit control throttling at the API level and per client with API Keys."},{"cat":"development","q":"Your application uses API Gateway REST API that needs to validate complex JSON schemas for incoming requests. Current validation is happening in Lambda. Where should this move?","options":["A. Keep in Lambda","B. Add request validators and models to API Gateway","C. Use API Gateway HTTP API instead","D. Add CloudFront validation"],"answer":1,"explain":"API Gateway request validators can reject invalid requests before reaching Lambda, reducing unnecessary invocations and improving response times."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to implement pagination for a DynamoDB query that can return thousands of results. The API should return batches of 50 items. What should you implement?","options":["A. Query all items and slice in Lambda","B. Use Query API with Limit parameter and ExclusiveStartKey for pagination","C. Use Scan operation with paging","D. Implement offset-based pagination"],"answer":1,"explain":"DynamoDB Query with Limit and ExclusiveStartKey enables efficient pagination without loading all items into memory."},{"cat":"apigateway","q":"Your API receives CSV requests but Lambda expects JSON. How should API Gateway handle conversion?","options":["A. Lambda must accept CSV","B. Use request mapping template to parse CSV into JSON structure","C. Create separate CSV and JSON endpoints","D. API Gateway cannot transform formats"],"answer":1,"explain":"VTL mapping templates can parse CSV, XML, or other formats and transform into Lambda-compatible structures."},{"cat":"apigateway","q":"An API method has a Lambda integration that returns status code 200 but API Gateway returns 500 to the client. What is the issue?","options":["A. Lambda function is broken","B. Lambda response format doesn't match expected statusCode/body structure in integration response","C. API Gateway instance is overloaded","D. CloudFront cache is stale"],"answer":1,"explain":"Lambda proxy integration expects {statusCode, body, headers} format; missing or malformed response causes 502 Bad Gateway or 500 errors."},{"cat":"apigateway","q":"You need to cache API responses for 5 minutes to reduce backend load. Where should caching be configured?","options":["A. In Lambda function","B. In API Gateway method response cache settings with TTL=300 seconds","C. Use CloudFront in front of API","D. Caching requires external database"],"answer":1,"explain":"API Gateway method caching with TTL caches responses per cache key (query params, headers), reducing backend invocations."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"RDS connection pooling causes Lambda to exhaust connections. What should you do?","options":["A. Increase RDS max_connections","B. Use RDS Proxy between Lambda and database","C. Reduce Lambda concurrency","D. A or B"],"answer":3,"explain":"RDS Proxy manages connection pools efficiently, allowing more Lambda concurrencies with fewer DB connections."},{"cat":"development","q":"Your Lambda function creates temporary files during processing. You need to ensure cleanup happens even if processing fails. What is the best approach?","options":["A. Delete files at the end of handler","B. Use try/finally to ensure cleanup in finally block","C. Set /tmp to auto-cleanup","D. Use Lambda layers for cleanup"],"answer":1,"explain":"try/finally ensures cleanup code executes regardless of success or failure, preventing file accumulation and /tmp exhaustion across invocations."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to prevent duplicate processing of SQS messages. Currently some messages are processed twice. What should you implement?","options":["A. Decrease SQS visibility timeout","B. Implement idempotency using message IDs and a tracking table","C. Use FIFO queues only","D. Increase Lambda concurrency"],"answer":1,"explain":"Idempotency using message ID tracking in DynamoDB ensures that duplicate message delivery does not result in duplicate processing."},{"cat":"development","q":"Your Lambda function needs to make 100+ API calls to gather data for a response. Each call takes 100ms. Current approach is too slow. What should you refactor to?","options":["A. Increase Lambda memory and timeout","B. Make calls in parallel using Promise.all()","C. Cache results in ElastiCache","D. Move to Step Functions"],"answer":1,"explain":"Parallel API calls using Promise.all() can reduce 10+ seconds of sequential time to ~100ms, vastly improving performance."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"SQS batch processing shows some messages failing. Should you delete failed messages?","options":["A. Delete immediately","B. Report partial batch failure to continue with next batch","C. Send to DLQ and retry","D. Depends on error type"],"answer":3,"explain":"Failed messages should either be retried, sent to DLQ, or requeued based on error type."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to create an API that accepts large file uploads. What is the maximum request payload size for API Gateway?","options":["A. 1 MB","B. 10 MB","C. 50 MB","D. 100 MB"],"answer":0,"explain":"API Gateway supports request payloads up to 10 MB; larger files should use S3 pre-signed URLs."},{"cat":"apigateway","q":"Your API Gateway REST API has CORS enabled but requests from a web app still fail with CORS errors. What headers should be checked?","options":["A. Content-Type header","B. Access-Control-Allow-Origin and Access-Control-Allow-Methods response headers","C. Authorization header only","D. X-API-Key header"],"answer":1,"explain":"CORS requires proper response headers including Access-Control-Allow-Origin, Methods, and Headers for browser requests."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You are deploying an application using Terraform. Should you use Terraform or CloudFormation?","options":["A. Terraform only","B. CloudFormation only","C. Both are equivalent, choose based on preference","D. Neither is suitable"],"answer":2,"explain":"Both are IaC tools; choose based on your infrastructure needs and team expertise."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Lambda environment variables contain sensitive data. How should you protect them?","options":["A. Encrypt them at rest using KMS","B. Store in Secrets Manager instead","C. Don't log environment variables","D. A and C"],"answer":3,"explain":"Use Secrets Manager for sensitive data and ensure sensitive variables aren't logged."},{"cat":"apigateway","q":"An API Gateway endpoint processes requests from multiple clients with different API keys for billing/tracking purposes. How should keys be managed?","options":["A. Include keys in URL query parameter","B. Use Usage Plans associated with API Keys; API Gateway validates keys per request","C. Embed keys in Lambda function","D. Use only Basic Auth with username/password"],"answer":1,"explain":"Usage Plans + API Keys enable per-client quota tracking, rate limiting, and billing without modifying Lambda logic."},{"cat":"apigateway","q":"You deploy a new API version but existing clients still call the old version. How should multiple versions coexist with different backends?","options":["A. Deprecate old version immediately","B. Use API Gateway stages (dev, prod, v2) with different integrations or stage variables for version routing","C. Deploy new API with different domain","D. Redirect all requests to new version"],"answer":1,"explain":"API Gateway stages + stage variables enable version management and gradual migration without breaking existing clients."},{"cat":"cognito","q":"In Cognito User Pool, you need to customize the confirmation email message sent to users. What trigger should be used?","options":["A. Pre-authentication trigger","B. Custom message trigger to modify message templates","C. Post-confirmation trigger","D. Pre-sign-up trigger"],"answer":1,"explain":"Custom message trigger allows modification of email/SMS content for confirmation, password reset, and other message types."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"API Gateway logs show high error rate from a specific client IP. How should you respond?","options":["A. Block the IP using WAF","B. Throttle the IP using API Gateway throttling","C. Investigate if it's legitimate traffic or an attack","D. A or B"],"answer":3,"explain":"First investigate whether the traffic is legitimate before taking protective actions."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to parse CloudFormation custom resource requests in Lambda. What is the response format?","options":["A. Standard HTTP 200","B. JSON with Status, PhysicalResourceId, Data fields sent to S3","C. CloudFormation event JSON","D. Any JSON response"],"answer":0,"explain":"Custom resource Lambda handlers must respond with specific JSON format including Status, PhysicalResourceId."},{"cat":"cognito","q":"A Cognito User Pool needs to enforce multi-factor authentication (MFA) for users in the 'admin' group. Where should this policy be defined?","options":["A. User Pool policies section","B. Pre-authentication Lambda trigger to check group membership and enforce MFA","C. Cognito Identity Pool role mapping","D. IAM policy attached to user account"],"answer":1,"explain":"Pre-authentication trigger can inspect user groups and challenge users for MFA before authentication succeeds."},{"cat":"cognito","q":"You want to automatically assign new Cognito users to a default group upon signup. What trigger should be configured?","options":["A. Pre-sign-up trigger","B. Post-confirmation trigger to add user to group after email verification","C. Custom authentication flow","D. Manual group assignment only"],"answer":1,"explain":"Post-confirmation trigger fires after user confirms email; use it to programmatically add user to default group."},{"cat":"security","q":"Your Lambda function needs to access database passwords. Currently they are stored in environment variables. What is the secure alternative?","options":["A. Store in Lambda code","B. Store encrypted in environment variables","C. Use Secrets Manager with automatic rotation","D. Store in S3"],"answer":2,"explain":"Secrets Manager provides automatic credential rotation, audit logging, and fine-grained IAM permissions without exposing secrets in environment variables."},{"cat":"cognito","q":"A developer needs to obtain temporary AWS credentials for an authenticated Cognito user to access S3. What Cognito feature is used?","options":["A. User Pool alone provides AWS credentials","B. Use Cognito Identity Pool (federated identity) to exchange Cognito token for AWS temporary credentials","C. IAM users for each Cognito user","D. Direct S3 access without credentials"],"answer":1,"explain":"Cognito Identity Pool exchanges ID token for temporary AWS credentials with scoped permissions via IAM role."},{"cat":"security","q":"You are implementing Cognito authentication for your API. Users should be able to authenticate via their corporate directory. Which Cognito feature enables this?","options":["A. Cognito user pools alone","B. Cognito identity pools","C. Identity providers (IdP) integration with Cognito user pools","D. Lambda authorizer"],"answer":2,"explain":"Cognito user pools support identity provider federation, allowing users to authenticate with SAML/OAuth providers like corporate directories."},{"cat":"security","q":"Your API requires mutual TLS (mTLS) for client authentication. How should you implement this in API Gateway?","options":["A. Enable mutual authentication with client certificates","B. Use Lambda authorizers","C. Use WAF","D. Use Cognito instead"],"answer":0,"explain":"API Gateway client certificate authentication validates client certificates and can pass certificate info to Lambda authorizers for authorization decisions."},{"cat":"security","q":"Your Lambda function calls KMS to decrypt sensitive data on every invocation. This adds latency. How should you optimize?","options":["A. Cache decrypted values in memory within the Lambda container","B. Disable KMS encryption","C. Use Data Key Caching with the KMS SDK","D. Use Secrets Manager instead"],"answer":2,"explain":"KMS data key caching reduces API calls to KMS by reusing cached plaintext keys for a configurable period, improving performance and reducing costs."},{"cat":"cognito","q":"Your application authenticates users with Cognito User Pool and needs to know the user's email and custom attributes. Where should this information be retrieved?","options":["A. From the ID token claims","B. Call GetUser API to fetch user profile with email and custom attributes","C. Query DynamoDB for user attributes","D. User attributes are not accessible after login"],"answer":0,"explain":"ID token JWT contains user attributes as claims (email, custom attributes); decode it directly without extra API calls."},{"cat":"security","q":"You need to ensure that developers cannot accidentally commit AWS credentials to your Git repository. What should you implement?","options":["A. Manual code review","B. Client-side git hooks to scan for secrets","C. Use services like git-secrets or truffleHog","D. Store credentials in .gitignore"],"answer":2,"explain":"Automated secret scanning tools like truffleHog or git-secrets can detect credential patterns and prevent commits containing secrets."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your ECS task needs to pull a private Docker image from ECR. What must be configured?","options":["A. ECR repository permissions","B. ECS task execution role with ECR permissions","C. VPC endpoint for ECR","D. B and optionally C"],"answer":2,"explain":"Task execution role needs ECR read permissions; VPC endpoint is optional if using public ECR."},{"cat":"security","q":"Your application receives API requests from multiple client IPs. Some appear to be scanning for vulnerabilities. How should you respond at the application layer?","options":["A. Log all requests for later analysis","B. Rate limit based on client IP using API Gateway throttling","C. Block at WAF level based on patterns","D. Both B and C"],"answer":3,"explain":"Use WAF for pattern-based blocking of malicious requests, and API Gateway throttling for rate-based protection against scanning and DoS."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to pass large context data between Lambda functions. What should you use?","options":["A. Pass in event data directly","B. Store in DynamoDB and pass key reference","C. Use S3 with event containing key","D. B or C depending on size"],"answer":0,"explain":"For large data, store in DynamoDB/S3 and pass references to avoid Lambda payload limits."},{"cat":"cognito","q":"You implement Cognito authentication with app client settings requiring a callback URL. What is this for?","options":["A. Redirect after logout only","B. OAuth callback URL where Cognito sends authorization code after user approves; app exchanges code for tokens","C. Health check endpoint","D. Not needed for User Pool"],"answer":1,"explain":"Callback URL is the OAuth redirect endpoint; Cognito sends auth code there, app exchanges it for tokens."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You need to run database migrations before deploying new code. When should this happen?","options":["A. After deployment completes","B. Before deployment using Lambda or container","C. In a separate pipeline stage","D. B or C"],"answer":2,"explain":"Run migrations before deployment using Lambda functions or containers in a dedicated stage."},{"cat":"cognito","q":"A Cognito User Pool is integrated with a third-party identity provider (OIDC). Users logging in via OIDC should have specific IAM permissions. How are these assigned?","options":["A. OIDC automatically grants permissions","B. Use Cognito Identity Pool with role mapping to assign IAM role based on external provider","C. Create separate IAM users for each provider","D. Permissions cannot be granted for external identity providers"],"answer":1,"explain":"Identity Pool role mapping associates IAM roles with OIDC provider attributes, granting AWS permissions after external auth."},{"cat":"cognito","q":"Your Cognito user pool has a password policy requiring special characters. A user's password reset email contains a temporary password. Is this temporary password subject to the policy?","options":["A. No, temporary passwords bypass policy","B. Yes, temporary passwords must still meet policy requirements and user must change it on first login","C. Temporary passwords are invalid after 1 hour","D. No policy check is performed"],"answer":1,"explain":"Temporary passwords meet policy requirements and must be changed on first login for security."},{"cat":"sqs","q":"Your SQS queue processes orders and needs to include order ID and priority with each message. What is the appropriate mechanism?","options":["A. Put order ID and priority in the message body as plain text","B. Use message attributes to store structured metadata like order ID and priority","C. Create separate queues for different priority levels","D. Store metadata in DynamoDB with message ID"],"answer":1,"explain":"Message attributes provide structured metadata storage without polluting the message body, enabling filtering and sorting."},{"cat":"security","q":"Your Lambda function reads JSON Web Tokens (JWT) from API requests. It currently validates the signature manually. Which approach is more secure?","options":["A. Manual validation in Lambda","B. Use Lambda authorizer to validate JWTs at API Gateway level","C. Skip validation","D. Both A and B are equal"],"answer":1,"explain":"Lambda authorizers validate tokens before invoking the Lambda function, preventing unauthorized Lambda invocations and caching authorization decisions."},{"cat":"security","q":"You need to log API request/response bodies for debugging but must not log sensitive fields like passwords. How should you implement this?","options":["A. Log everything","B. Do not log sensitive data; filter/mask it in CloudWatch Logs","C. Store logs in S3 encrypted","D. Use VPC Flow Logs instead"],"answer":1,"explain":"Implement field masking/filtering in logging code to prevent sensitive data from being written to CloudWatch Logs and accessible to other teams."},{"cat":"security","q":"Your API Gateway is protected by a Lambda authorizer. The authorizer caches the decision. What is a security concern with token-based caching?","options":["A. Tokens cannot be revoked quickly","B. Token revocation is delayed by cache TTL","C. Stolen tokens are valid for full cache duration","D. All of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"Cached authorization decisions mean token revocation does not take effect immediately. Balance cache TTL with security requirements for token revocation."},{"cat":"security","q":"What is the difference between authentication headers and authorization headers?","options":["A. They are the same","B. Authentication proves who you are, authorization proves what you can do","C. Only one is necessary","D. Both are optional"],"answer":1,"explain":"Authentication verifies identity; authorization determines resource access permissions."},{"cat":"sqs","q":"You need to send 50 messages to SQS in your application. Individual SendMessage calls cause high latency. What operation should be used?","options":["A. Use SendMessage in a loop","B. Use SendMessageBatch to send up to 10 messages per request","C. Use PutMessage instead of SendMessage","D. Buffer in DynamoDB first, then send to SQS"],"answer":1,"explain":"SendMessageBatch reduces API calls and latency by bundling up to 10 messages into a single request."},{"cat":"security","q":"You need to call AWS APIs from a JavaScript web application. Using IAM user credentials in JavaScript is insecure. What should you use?","options":["A. Store credentials in localStorage","B. Cognito Identity pools to obtain temporary STS credentials","C. API keys","D. Root account credentials"],"answer":1,"explain":"Cognito Identity pools provide temporary AWS credentials with limited permissions, avoiding the need for long-term credentials in client applications."},{"cat":"security","q":"Your application needs to integrate with a third-party service that requires API key authentication. How should you store this key securely in your Lambda?","options":["A. Hardcode in Lambda function","B. Store in environment variable","C. Store in AWS Secrets Manager","D. Pass via API Gateway"],"answer":2,"explain":"Secrets Manager provides encryption, audit logging, automatic rotation support, and fine-grained access control for third-party credentials."},{"cat":"sqs","q":"Your SQS consumer polls the queue every 0.1 seconds but usually gets 0 messages. This causes high API call costs. What optimization reduces costs?","options":["A. Increase polling frequency to every 1 second","B. Enable long polling with WaitTimeSeconds=20 to reduce empty responses","C. Use SNS instead of SQS","D. Reduce message visibility timeout"],"answer":1,"explain":"Long polling waits up to 20 seconds for messages before returning, dramatically reducing API calls and associated costs."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You need to deploy multiple environments from one CodePipeline. What should you use?","options":["A. Multiple pipelines","B. Manual approval stages between environments","C. Separate CodeDeploy applications","D. A and B"],"answer":2,"explain":"Use manual approvals to control promotion through environments; can use separate applications."},{"cat":"security","q":"You implemented an API endpoint that allows querying user data by ID. Currently anyone can query any user ID. What authorization should you add?","options":["A. No authorization needed if API is behind API Gateway","B. Implement attribute-based access control (ABAC) checking user permissions in Lambda","C. Check if requesting user owns the resource","D. A and B"],"answer":2,"explain":"Implement authorization checks in Lambda to ensure users can only access their own resources (or what they have permission for), preventing horizontal privilege escalation."},{"cat":"security","q":"Your API Gateway uses OAuth 2.0 for authentication. How should you validate the access token in your Lambda?","options":["A. Trust the token from API Gateway without validation","B. Validate token signature and expiration in Lambda","C. Call the OAuth provider to validate","D. Use CloudFront to validate"],"answer":1,"explain":"Validate token signature using the OAuth provider public keys and check token expiration in Lambda to prevent use of expired or tampered tokens."},{"cat":"sqs","q":"A message remains in SQS queue for 2 hours after processing but before being deleted. What is the issue?","options":["A. The queue is broken","B. Consumer received message but didn't delete it; visibility timeout expired and message became visible again","C. Message retention period is set to 2 hours","D. SQS requires manual deletion"],"answer":1,"explain":"Visibility timeout hides message from other consumers; consumer must delete it within timeout or it becomes visible again."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You are setting up a CI/CD pipeline with CodePipeline. The pipeline must deploy to both development and production accounts. What is required?","options":["A. Single pipeline with cross-account permissions","B. Separate pipeline for each account","C. Manual approval stages with cross-account role","D. A or C"],"answer":3,"explain":"Use cross-account IAM roles in CodeDeploy/CloudFormation to deploy from one pipeline to multiple accounts, with manual approvals for production."},{"cat":"sqs","q":"Your SQS queue has a visibility timeout of 5 seconds but processing takes 10 seconds. What happens?","options":["A. Processing completes successfully; timeout doesn't interrupt","B. After 5 seconds, message becomes visible to other consumers before first consumer finishes; potential duplicate processing","C. Processing is killed after 5 seconds","D. Message is deleted automatically"],"answer":1,"explain":"Low visibility timeout causes duplicate processing; increase timeout to exceed max processing time."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your CodeBuild project builds Docker images but the build times are increasing. After investigation, you find Docker layer caching is not working. What should you configure?","options":["A. Use buildspec.yml with docker buildx","B. Enable Docker layer caching in CodeBuild build environment","C. Use S3 for build caching","D. Upgrade CodeBuild to newer version"],"answer":1,"explain":"CodeBuild supports Docker layer caching by storing intermediate layers. Enable this in the project settings to reuse layers across builds."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You need to deploy an application to EC2 instances using CodeDeploy. Some instances fail during deployment. How should you handle partial deployment failure?","options":["A. Fail the entire deployment","B. Configure deployment preferences with OneAtATime to catch issues early","C. Use MinimumHealthyHosts to define acceptable failure threshold","D. Both B and C"],"answer":3,"explain":"Configure deployment configuration with MinimumHealthyHosts to allow partial failures while maintaining availability, or use canary deployments."},{"cat":"sqs","q":"An SQS consumer needs to process messages in the exact order they were sent. What should be configured?","options":["A. Standard queue processes in FIFO order","B. Use FIFO queue with message group ID for ordering guarantee","C. Enable message ordering in attributes","D. Order is not guaranteed in SQS"],"answer":1,"explain":"Only SQS FIFO queues guarantee message order; standard queues do not maintain order."},{"cat":"sqs","q":"You configure a dead letter queue (DLQ) for an SQS queue with max receive count=3. A message fails 3 times. What happens?","options":["A. Message is deleted","B. After 3 failed receive attempts, message is moved to DLQ for analysis","C. Processing stops for the queue","D. Message is retried indefinitely"],"answer":1,"explain":"Messages reaching max receive count are moved to DLQ; process DLQ messages for failure analysis and recovery."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your Elastic Beanstalk environment uses the default deployment policy but deployments cause downtime. Which deployment policy would eliminate downtime?","options":["A. All at once (current)","B. Rolling","C. Rolling with additional batch","D. Immutable or Blue/Green"],"answer":3,"explain":"Rolling, immutable, and blue/green deployments maintain availability during updates. All at once causes brief downtime."},{"cat":"sqs","q":"Your application needs to guarantee that each SQS message is processed exactly once. What pattern ensures this?","options":["A. Standard queue is sufficient","B. Use FIFO queue + idempotent processing logic + message deduplication ID","C. Disable retries","D. Exactly-once guarantee is impossible"],"answer":1,"explain":"FIFO + idempotency (tracking processed message IDs) guarantees exactly-once semantics despite potential retries."},{"cat":"codedeploy","q":"You're deploying a Lambda function with CodeDeploy and need to validate the new version before shifting all traffic. What AppSpec hooks enable this?","options":["A. BeforeDeploy and AfterDeploy hooks","B. BeforeAllowTraffic to validate and AfterAllowTraffic to confirm","C. PreHook and PostHook","D. StartHook and EndHook"],"answer":1,"explain":"Lambda deployment hooks allow validation of the new version (BeforeAllowTraffic) before shifting traffic (AfterAllowTraffic)."},{"cat":"codedeploy","q":"A CodeDeploy Lambda deployment uses Linear traffic shifting with 10% per minute. The deployment takes 15 minutes total. What is the traffic progression?","options":["A. 10%, 20%, 30%... 100% over 10 minutes","B. 10% every minute: 10%, 20%, 30%... 100% over 10 minutes","C. All traffic shifts to new version immediately","D. Traffic stays at 50/50 mix"],"answer":0,"explain":"Linear traffic shifting increments traffic by a fixed percentage each interval, allowing incremental validation."},{"cat":"codedeploy","q":"Your CodeDeploy configuration uses Canary traffic shifting. 5% of traffic goes to new version; if no errors in 10 minutes, remaining 95% shifts. What is the benefit?","options":["A. Faster deployments","B. Early error detection with minimal blast radius; rollback only affects 5%","C. No rollback needed","D. Cost reduction"],"answer":1,"explain":"Canary deployment minimizes blast radius; if new version fails, only 5% of traffic is affected before automatic rollback."},{"cat":"codedeploy","q":"A CodeDeploy EC2 deployment fails because the CodeDeploy agent is not running on the instance. How should this be configured?","options":["A. CodeDeploy agent should be pre-installed and running on all EC2 instances","B. CodeDeploy automatically installs the agent on first deployment","C. CodeDeploy doesn't need an agent on EC2","D. Agent should be installed manually after each deployment"],"answer":0,"explain":"CodeDeploy agent must be pre-installed and running on EC2 instances; it pulls and executes deployment scripts."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your Lambda function is deployed using SAM. You need to add a Lambda layer for shared code. How should you configure this in the SAM template?","options":["A. Use Layers property in Function resource","B. Create separate Lambda::Layer resource","C. Package layers separately","D. A or B"],"answer":3,"explain":"SAM supports both inline layer definitions and separate LayerVersion resources. Use either approach depending on your template organization."},{"cat":"codedeploy","q":"Your CodeDeploy deployment includes a custom deployment script in AppSpec that modifies application files. The script fails but deployment continues. What should be configured?","options":["A. Deployment always continues despite script failures","B. Set OnFailure=STOP in the hook configuration to stop deployment on script failure","C. Manually intervene to stop deployment","D. Script failures are ignored"],"answer":1,"explain":"AppSpec hooks can be configured with OnFailure=STOP to halt deployment if validation or setup scripts fail."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You are deploying infrastructure with AWS CDK. You need to reference outputs from another stack (database endpoint). How should you do this?","options":["A. Hardcode the endpoint","B. Use stack imports/exports or pass as constructor parameters","C. Use SSM Parameter Store","D. B or C"],"answer":3,"explain":"CDK stacks can use imports/exports for cross-stack references, or use Secrets Manager/Parameter Store for decoupled configuration."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your CodeDeploy deployment fails with \"permission denied\" writing to an S3 bucket. The AppSpec file references the bucket. What should you check?","options":["A. EC2 instance security group","B. IAM instance profile attached to EC2 instance","C. S3 bucket policy","D. B and C"],"answer":3,"explain":"EC2 instances need an IAM instance profile with S3 permissions. Also verify S3 bucket policy does not restrict access."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your Elastic Beanstalk environment needs to execute initialization scripts. Where should these be placed?","options":["A. In application code","B. In .ebextensions/commands.config","C. In boot scripts manually","D. Not possible in Beanstalk"],"answer":1,"explain":".ebextensions directory allows you to define commands, packages, and configuration that execute during environment creation and updates."},{"cat":"cloudformation","q":"You're using CloudFormation to deploy a serverless application. What AWS::Serverless resource defines an API endpoint?","options":["A. AWS::Serverless::Function","B. AWS::Serverless::Api with properties for routes and integrations","C. AWS::Serverless::Endpoint","D. AWS::ApiGateway::RestApi"],"answer":1,"explain":"AWS::Serverless::Api (SAM) is the simplified CloudFormation resource for API Gateway with automatic integration to Lambda."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to implement feature flags for gradual rollout. What service should you use?","options":["A. Lambda environment variables","B. AppConfig for centralized feature flag management","C. S3 configuration files","D. DynamoDB configuration table"],"answer":0,"explain":"AppConfig provides managed feature flag and configuration service with client library."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You need to deploy an updated Lambda function version but maintain backward compatibility. Clients still use the old version. What should you do?","options":["A. Delete old version","B. Create new version and use aliases to control which version gets traffic","C. Update function and increment version number manually","D. Use CloudFront versioning"],"answer":1,"explain":"Lambda aliases can point to different versions. Use gradual traffic shifting with aliases to migrate clients to new versions safely."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your CodePipeline has CodeBuild testing stage that generates a test report. You need to visualize test results. What should CodeBuild configure?","options":["A. CloudWatch Logs only","B. Report groups with test report output","C. Upload report to S3","D. Email reports"],"answer":1,"explain":"CodeBuild report groups generate test reports visible in CodePipeline and CodeBuild console, showing pass/fail/skipped test counts."},{"cat":"cloudformation","q":"A SAM template needs to grant a Lambda function permissions to read from S3 and write to DynamoDB. What section should be used?","options":["A. ManagedPolicyArns with AWS managed policies","B. Policies section with SAM policy templates like S3ReadPolicy and DynamoDBWritePolicy","C. IAM section of the template","D. Resource section for each AWS service"],"answer":1,"explain":"SAM policy templates provide shorthand permissions (e.g., S3ReadPolicy) without writing full IAM policy documents."},{"cat":"cloudformation","q":"Your CloudFormation template has circular dependency: Resource A depends on B, B depends on A. How is this resolved?","options":["A. CloudFormation automatically detects and resolves circular dependencies","B. Refactor template to break dependency cycle; use DependsOn only when implicit dependencies don't work","C. Create separate stacks for A and B","D. Circular dependencies are impossible"],"answer":1,"explain":"CloudFormation cannot resolve circular dependencies; refactor template structure to eliminate them."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You are deploying containerized applications with CloudFormation. You need to update container image without updating the CloudFormation stack. What should you use?","options":["A. Update the stack","B. Update ECS service to pull new image tag","C. Restart containers manually","D. Redeploy entire stack"],"answer":1,"explain":"ECS services can be updated to pull new image versions independently of CloudFormation stack updates using the UpdateService API."},{"cat":"cloudformation","q":"A CloudFormation stack creation fails partway through. You fix the issue and try to create again with the same stack name. What happens?","options":["A. Creation succeeds with the corrected template","B. Stack is in CREATE_FAILED state and must be deleted before recreating","C. CloudFormation automatically cleans up and retries","D. New stack is created with a different name"],"answer":1,"explain":"Failed stacks must be deleted before creating a new stack with the same name to avoid resource conflicts."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your application uses SAM with LocalStack for local development. How should developers test Lambda and DynamoDB locally?","options":["A. Use sam local start-api and sam local start-dynamodb","B. Only test in AWS","C. Use Docker Compose with AWS services","D. A or C"],"answer":3,"explain":"SAM CLI provides local testing environments for Lambda and other services. LocalStack or Docker Compose enables local AWS service emulation."},{"cat":"cloudformation","q":"Your SAM template defines multiple Lambda functions sharing common code. How should shared code be packaged?","options":["A. Duplicate code in each function","B. Package shared code as a Lambda layer; reference in Layers property","C. Use nested stacks for each function","D. Shared code is not possible"],"answer":1,"explain":"Lambda layers contain shared code/dependencies; multiple functions reference the same layer, reducing duplication."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your CodePipeline deployment to production failed mid-way through. You need to rollback to the previous version. What should you do?","options":["A. Re-run the failed action in CodePipeline","B. Manually rollback infrastructure","C. Use CodeDeploy rollback with previous appspec","D. A or C"],"answer":3,"explain":"Re-running the previous successful pipeline execution or using CodeDeploy automatic rollback can restore the previous version depending on the failure."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your Lambda deployment package is 250MB. SAM packaging fails because it exceeds the direct upload limit. How should you handle this?","options":["A. Split into multiple functions","B. Upload to S3 first, then reference in SAM template","C. Use Lambda layers for dependencies","D. B or C"],"answer":3,"explain":"SAM can reference packages in S3. Alternatively, separate dependencies into layers that are uploaded to S3."},{"cat":"cloudformation","q":"A CloudFormation stack includes a database resource with DeletionPolicy=Retain. Stack deletion fails because of remaining resources. What happens to the database?","options":["A. Database is deleted automatically","B. Database is retained even after stack deletion for data preservation","C. Stack cannot be deleted","D. Database is backed up before deletion"],"answer":1,"explain":"DeletionPolicy=Retain preserves resources after stack deletion; useful for databases and backups to prevent accidental loss."},{"cat":"elasticache","q":"Your application caches user sessions in ElastiCache Redis. When the cache is cold, database load spikes. What caching pattern mitigates this?","options":["A. Write-through: always write to cache and database together","B. Lazy loading: populate cache on cache miss, avoiding stampedes","C. Cache invalidation: clear cache periodically","D. TTL only without application-side caching"],"answer":0,"explain":"Write-through ensures database and cache are always in sync, preventing cache misses and database flooding."},{"cat":"elasticache","q":"An ElastiCache cluster has an eviction policy of allkeys-lru (evict any key using LRU). Application performance degrades after memory is full. What is happening?","options":["A. The cluster is undersized and needs larger instance type","B. Keys are being evicted when memory is full, causing increased cache misses and database hits","C. LRU policy is not effective for session data","D. Memory usage monitoring is not enabled"],"answer":1,"explain":"eviction-lru removes least recently used keys when maxmemory is exceeded, increasing cache misses and database load."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your application requires a specific version of a dependency. How should you manage this?","options":["A. Let dependency manager choose latest","B. Pin specific version in requirements/package file","C. Install multiple versions","D. Don't use dependency management"],"answer":2,"explain":"Pinning dependency versions ensures reproducible builds and predictable behavior."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You need to deploy updates to an Elastic Beanstalk environment without affecting users. What deployment option should you use?","options":["A. All at once","B. Rolling","C. Immutable","D. Blue/Green"],"answer":3,"explain":"Immutable and blue/green deployments launch a complete new environment, ensuring old environment stays active until new one is verified healthy."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to create a Lambda function that processes events from multiple sources. What pattern should you use?","options":["A. Separate function per source","B. Single function with event type routing","C. Use EventBridge for routing only","D. Use Lambda aliases"],"answer":0,"explain":"A single function with event type handling reduces complexity and deployment overhead."},{"cat":"elasticache","q":"You're caching product catalog data in ElastiCache with 1-hour TTL. Updates to products are infrequent but must be reflected immediately. What is the issue?","options":["A. One-hour TTL is fine for product data","B. TTL-based expiration causes stale data; use cache invalidation on product update instead","C. Cache invalidation is too expensive","D. Products should not be cached"],"answer":1,"explain":"Event-driven cache invalidation (on product update) prevents stale data better than fixed TTLs for infrequent changes."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"You need to deploy infrastructure only to specific AWS regions. How should you handle this?","options":["A. Hardcode region in template","B. Use CloudFormation parameters for regions","C. Replicate templates per region manually","D. AWS doesn't support multi-region"],"answer":2,"explain":"CloudFormation parameters allow flexible region deployment without code changes."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your Lambda function is invoked 1000 times per second but many invocations timeout. You already increased the timeout to 900 seconds. What is the likely issue?","options":["A. Lambda is too slow","B. Lambda concurrency is throttled","C. DynamoDB is slow","D. API Gateway is rejecting requests"],"answer":1,"explain":"If many functions timeout despite sufficient timeout setting, the issue is likely concurrency throttling or downstream service limitations, not Lambda speed."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to call a service that requires client certificates. How should you store the certificate?","options":["A. In Lambda environment variable","B. In Secrets Manager with rotation","C. Hardcoded in function code","D. In S3 public bucket"],"answer":0,"explain":"Secrets Manager provides secure storage with encryption for client certificates."},{"cat":"elasticache","q":"An ElastiCache Redis cluster uses Memcached protocol. Multi-threaded client connections fail. What is the issue?","options":["A. Memcached doesn't support multi-threaded clients","B. Use Redis instead of Memcached for better multi-threaded support","C. Configure connection pooling in the client","D. Memcached and Redis are the same"],"answer":1,"explain":"Redis supports pipelining and multi-threaded clients better; Memcached is simpler but less flexible for concurrent operations."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"API Gateway shows 502 Bad Gateway errors intermittently for a Lambda authorizer. Authorizer logs show no errors. What should you investigate?","options":["A. Lambda authorizer performance/timeout","B. Lambda authorizer response format","C. CloudWatch Logs configuration","D. API Gateway throttling limits"],"answer":1,"explain":"502 errors from authorizers indicate timeout or invalid response format. Check if authorizer is exceeding the 29-second integration timeout."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your DynamoDB table has high read throttling errors despite adequate provisioned capacity. CloudWatch shows capacity is unused. What could cause this?","options":["A. Partition hot spots from uneven key distribution","B. GSI is under-provisioned","C. DynamoDB streams consuming capacity","D. A or B"],"answer":3,"explain":"Hot partitions from skewed key distribution cause throttling on specific partitions even if aggregate capacity is available. GSIs have separate capacity provisioning."},{"cat":"elasticache","q":"You configure ElastiCache cluster with automatic failover enabled. The primary node fails. What happens?","options":["A. All cached data is lost","B. Replica is promoted to primary; applications switch to new primary automatically with minimal downtime","C. Manual intervention is required","D. Cluster goes offline permanently"],"answer":1,"explain":"Multi-AZ with automatic failover promotes replica to primary, maintaining availability without application code changes."},{"cat":"kinesis","q":"You're streaming clickstream data to Kinesis with millions of users. Each record contains user ID. How should partition keys be chosen?","options":["A. Use timestamp as partition key for temporal ordering","B. Use user ID as partition key to distribute load evenly","C. Use a random value to load-balance across shards","D. Use the same key for all records"],"answer":1,"explain":"User ID as partition key distributes traffic across shards and keeps a user's events on the same shard for ordering."},{"cat":"kinesis","q":"A Kinesis consumer needs to read all records from the beginning of a stream. What GetShardIterator type should be used?","options":["A. LATEST to get the newest records","B. TRIM_HORIZON to read from the oldest retained record","C. AT_TIMESTAMP to read from a specific time","D. NEW_IMAGE to get only changed records"],"answer":1,"explain":"TRIM_HORIZON (oldest retained record, typically 24 hours) is used for complete replays; LATEST starts from new records."},{"cat":"kinesis","q":"Your Kinesis stream has 10 shards and processes 100,000 records per second. One shard falls behind others. What is the issue?","options":["A. All shards should process equally","B. Partition key distribution is uneven, causing hot shard; choose better partition key","C. Kinesis has insufficient capacity","D. Consumer is too slow"],"answer":1,"explain":"Uneven partition key distribution creates hot shards that exceed their throughput capacity while others are underutilized."},{"cat":"kinesis","q":"You send records to Kinesis with PutRecord and experience ProvisionedThroughputExceededException. What operation handles multiple records more efficiently?","options":["A. Use PutRecord multiple times","B. Use PutRecords to batch up to 500 records in a single request","C. Use Kinesis Firehose instead","D. Increase shard count immediately"],"answer":1,"explain":"PutRecords batches records, reducing API calls and improving throughput compared to individual PutRecord calls."},{"cat":"kinesis","q":"A Kinesis consumer processes records every 5 seconds but records arrive continuously. Processing lags behind ingestion. What is the issue?","options":["A. Kinesis is too slow","B. Consumer parallelism is insufficient; use multiple consumers or increase batch size for faster processing","C. Records are queued indefinitely","D. Kinesis cannot handle high throughput"],"answer":1,"explain":"Consumer throughput must match or exceed producer rate; increase consumers, parallelism, or batch processing for catch-up."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your Lambda function's dependencies have conflicting versions. How should you resolve this?","options":["A. Use multiple deployment packages","B. Use Lambda layers to separate concerns","C. Update all to latest version","D. Remove conflicting dependency"],"answer":2,"explain":"Lambda layers help manage dependency conflicts by separating code from libraries."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"CodeBuild buildspec.yml defines environment variables. Secrets appear as plain text in build logs. How should you secure this?","options":["A. Do not log environment variables","B. Use secrets_manager or parameter_store in buildspec","C. Store secrets in Systems Manager Parameter Store","D. All of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"CodeBuild can retrieve secrets from Secrets Manager or Parameter Store; configure buildspec to avoid logging sensitive output; use buildspec secrets handling."},{"cat":"development","q":"You need to generate unique identifiers that are sortable by time. What should you use?","options":["A. Timestamp + random number","B. UUID v1 (time-based)","C. Sequential numeric IDs","D. UUIDv4"],"answer":0,"explain":"UUIDv1 combines timestamp with uniqueness, providing sortable unique identifiers."},{"cat":"xray","q":"Your microservices are instrumented with X-Ray. A distributed trace shows long latency in the downstream service. How should you trace internal operations?","options":["A. Use X-Ray annotations to tag high-level information","B. Create X-Ray subsegments to measure specific operations within the service","C. Add more logging to CloudWatch","D. Use CloudTrail to audit API calls"],"answer":1,"explain":"Subsegments break down service execution into named operations (database queries, API calls), revealing where latency occurs."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your Lambda function writes to CloudWatch Logs but logs are not appearing. Lambda has sufficient memory and timeout. What should you verify?","options":["A. CloudWatch Logs group exists","B. Lambda execution role has logs:CreateLogGroup, logs:CreateLogStream, logs:PutLogEvents","C. Function is actually being invoked","D. All of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"Lambda needs explicit IAM permissions to write logs. Verify the execution role policy includes CloudWatch Logs permissions and function is being called."},{"cat":"xray","q":"You need to filter X-Ray traces to see only those with errors. Where should error information be added to the trace?","options":["A. In the response object returned to the client","B. Add error=true as metadata in the trace segment","C. Use CloudWatch Logs Insights to search error traces","D. Use annotations with error flags for filtering"],"answer":3,"explain":"Annotations are indexed and filterable in X-Ray console, making them ideal for error flags, status codes, and custom tags."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your Cognito user pool shows failed login attempts from a specific IP. You need to block this IP from further attempts. What should you configure?","options":["A. Security group (does not apply to Cognito)","B. WAF rule for the Cognito domain","C. Cognito password policy","D. Lambda trigger for custom block logic"],"answer":3,"explain":"Cognito Lambda triggers can implement custom logic to block IPs after repeated failures. WAF can also block at the application layer."},{"cat":"xray","q":"X-Ray sampling is set to 1% of requests. Production experiences an outage but only 1% of traces are captured. How can this be improved?","options":["A. Sampling rate is sufficient","B. Use sampling rules to increase rate for errors/exceptions or sample 100% of errors","C. Disable sampling entirely","D. X-Ray cannot sample selectively"],"answer":1,"explain":"Sampling rules allow higher rates for specific paths/status codes; always sample errors (100%) for complete failure visibility."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"EventBridge rule processes events but some fail to invoke the target Lambda. Failed events are not retried. What should you verify?","options":["A. Lambda permissions allow EventBridge to invoke","B. Event pattern matches actual events","C. EventBridge retry policy is configured","D. All of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"EventBridge requires proper resource-based permissions, correct event pattern matching, and retry/DLQ configuration to handle failures."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your SQS messages are being processed multiple times by the same Lambda. What is the likely cause?","options":["A. Lambda timeout causes message to reappear","B. SQS visibility timeout is too short","C. Lambda is not deleting messages after processing","D. All of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"Messages reappear if Lambda times out before deleting, visibility timeout expires prematurely, or Lambda crashes without deletion confirmation."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your Step Functions state machine execution fails with \"States.Permissions\" error. The state machine cannot invoke a Lambda function. What should you check?","options":["A. Step Functions execution role has Lambda invoke permissions","B. Lambda resource policy allows Step Functions","C. Lambda function exists","D. A and B"],"answer":3,"explain":"Step Functions needs both IAM role permissions to invoke Lambda AND Lambda needs resource-based policy allowing Step Functions to invoke it."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"API Gateway is throttling requests returning 429 errors. You configured usage plan and API key but throttling still occurs. Where else should you check?","options":["A. API Gateway default throttling limits","B. Stage-level throttling settings","C. Request path-level throttling","D. All of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"API Gateway throttling can be configured at multiple levels: account (default), stage, and usage plan. Check all levels to identify the bottleneck."},{"cat":"deployment","q":"Your CloudFormation template needs conditional resource creation. How should you do this?","options":["A. Conditions section in template","B. Create multiple templates","C. Hardcode logic in Lambda","D. Conditions are not supported"],"answer":2,"explain":"CloudFormation Conditions enable conditional resource creation based on parameters."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your RDS database connection from Lambda works occasionally but often fails with \"too many connections\" error. You increased max_connections but still fails. What should you do?","options":["A. Increase RDS instance size","B. Use RDS Proxy to pool connections","C. Create more database replicas","D. Move to DynamoDB"],"answer":1,"explain":"RDS Proxy maintains a connection pool and provides connections to Lambda functions, preventing connection exhaustion from many concurrent Lambda invocations."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your CloudFormation stack creation fails with a rollback. The error message is generic. How should you investigate the failure?","options":["A. Check CloudFormation Events tab for detailed error messages","B. Check resource-specific logs (Lambda, CodeBuild, etc.)","C. Look at CloudTrail for API errors","D. All of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"CloudFormation Events show what failed, individual service logs show why, and CloudTrail shows API-level errors. Use all three for complete troubleshooting."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"X-Ray tracing is enabled on your Lambda function but you do not see traces in the console. What is the most common cause?","options":["A. X-Ray daemon is not running","B. Lambda execution role lacks x-ray:PutTraceSegments permission","C. X-Ray is not enabled in API Gateway","D. Lambda is in a VPC"],"answer":1,"explain":"Lambda needs IAM permissions to write trace segments to X-Ray. Without proper permissions, traces will not be sent even if X-Ray is enabled."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your ECS task fails to start with no meaningful error logs. Where should you look first?","options":["A. CloudWatch Logs for the task","B. ECS task stopped reason","C. Container logs in the container runtime","D. B and C"],"answer":3,"explain":"ECS stopped reason shows why the task stopped (container exit code, resource issues). Container logs show application errors. Check both."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"CodeDeploy deployment completes with \"Successful\" but your application is still running the old version. What should you investigate?","options":["A. CodeDeploy agent is running","B. ApplicationStart lifecycle hook in AppSpec is actually restarting the application","C. Application caching is serving old version","D. B and C"],"answer":3,"explain":"Verify ApplicationStart script in AppSpec actually stops old and starts new version. Also check if application caching or browser caching is serving old code."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your SQS DLQ accumulates messages but you do not know what went wrong. How should you debug DLQ messages?","options":["A. Receive messages and parse SQS Attributes (ApproximateReceiveCount, SentTimestamp)","B. Check SendMessageAttributes for original error info","C. Create Lambda to process DLQ and log messages","D. All of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"Receive DLQ messages, inspect attributes and content, create Lambda to log/process them. ApproximateReceiveCount shows retry attempts."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"API Gateway custom domain certificate shows \"Certificate Mismatch\" error. The certificate was just created. What should you check?","options":["A. Certificate domain matches the custom domain name","B. Certificate is in \"Issued\" status (not pending)","C. ACM certificate is in us-east-1 region","D. All of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"API Gateway custom domains require ACM certificates in us-east-1, with domain names that match exactly, and must be fully issued."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your Secrets Manager secret retrieval from Lambda suddenly starts failing with \"AccessDenied\". The Lambda function has not changed. What should you check?","options":["A. Lambda execution role IAM policy","B. Secrets Manager secret policy","C. Lambda VPC endpoint access to Secrets Manager","D. All of the above"],"answer":3,"explain":"Check Lambda execution role permissions, secret resource policy, and if Lambda is in VPC, ensure endpoint or NAT access to Secrets Manager."},{"cat":"troubleshooting","q":"Your DynamoDB table occasionally shows \"TransactionConflictException\" when using TransactWriteItems. What does this mean?","options":["A. Write capacity exceeded","B. Multiple transactions trying to modify same item","C. DynamoDB is unreachable","D. Encryption key issue"],"answer":1,"explain":"TransactionConflictException occurs when concurrent transactions try to modify the same item. Implement retry logic with exponential backoff."}];